This paper is primarily focused on the design and training of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sparse layers is a technique to reduce computation requirements, which is relevant to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also experiments with convolutional layers, which are commonly used in computer vision applications (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential of sparse networks to improve performance, which is a key goal in artificial intelligence research (cs.AI). Finally, the paper explores the properties of sparse network structures, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity and cryptography (cs.SI).
